DASALL on Ubuntu
================

This package installs the DASALL daemon but does not start it automatically
on first install.

First deployment steps
----------------------

1. P0 operator path is root/sudo-only.
   Run the installed operator workflow as: sudo dasall config

2. Canonical files remain:
   - /etc/default/dasall-daemon for profile selection
   - /etc/dasall/daemon.json for daemon.* overrides

3. Validate the deployment configuration:

	. /etc/default/dasall-daemon && /usr/sbin/dasall-daemon --validate-only --profile-id="${DASALL_DAEMON_PROFILE_ID}" --config-file /etc/dasall/daemon.json

4. Enable and start the daemon explicitly:

   systemctl enable --now dasall-daemon.service

5. Verify the service:

   systemctl status dasall-daemon.service
   sudo dasall ping --json

Runtime paths
-------------

Read-only assets: /usr/share/dasall/
Configuration:    /etc/default/dasall-daemon and /etc/dasall/daemon.json
Runtime socket:   /run/dasall/daemon.sock
State data:       /var/lib/dasall/

Local CLI access
----------------

The installed command name is dasall. The source-tree name dasall-cli is not
part of the package-facing operator surface.

The v1 operator path is root/sudo-only. Use sudo dasall for local daemon
operations until a future non-root access model is explicitly introduced.